    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B03",
      "act": "THE PROBLEM",
      "t_start": 19,
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "A parabolic wavefunction in a box is a sum of standing-wave modes. Each mode spins its phase at a rate proportional to n squared \u2014 faster and faster for higher modes.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "accumulate"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-quantum-revival/mp3/beat-B03.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 10.95,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-quantum-revival/clips/B03.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-quantum-revival/mp3/beat-B03.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B04",
      "act": "THE PROBLEM",
      "t_start": 30,
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "narration_text": "At first the modes walk in step. Then they drift: the fast ones race ahead, the slow ones lag behind. The probability density churns into an incoherent smear.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "decay"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-quantum-revival/mp3/beat-B04.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 10.34,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-quantum-revival/clips/B04.mp4",
      "source_audio": "../vox-quantum-revival/mp3/beat-B04.mp3"
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B05",
      "act": "THE MECHANISM",
      "t_start": 40,
      "estimated_duration_s": 12,
      "narration_text": "The key: the mode frequencies are n-squared times a base rate. All ratios of those frequencies are rational numbers. That means the clocks are commensurable \u2014 they will all realign.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "compare"
      },
      "audio_file": "../vox-quantum-revival/mp3/beat-B05.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 10.45,
      "locked": true,
      "source_clip": "../vox-quantum-revival/clips/B05.mp4",
